  "notes": "Kirundi (Rundi, Bantu JD62), Latin orthography. ⟨c⟩ = /tʃ/, ⟨j⟩ = /ɟ/, ⟨sh⟩ = /ʃ/, ⟨ny⟩ = /ɲ/, ⟨y⟩ = /j/, ⟨r⟩ = flap [ɾ]. Vowel length is phonemic and written by doubling the vowel (aa, ee, …); tone (H/L) is phonemic but is NOT written in the standard orthography, so no tone can be recovered from spelling alone.",
